headline.main: NEW TANKS IN FIELD; New Zealand Units Also Reach Scene of Chief Battle in Libya

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 26 -- The British Middle East Command announced in Cairo today that strong British tank reinforcements had arrived at forward areas in Libya "where our armored formations are rapidly reorganizing, after five days of continuous fighting, to resume their part in the main operation around Rezegh."
abstract: Brit tank reinforcements arrive Libya forward areas; N Z troops drive westward toward Rezegh; Brit move eastward from Tobruk; Axis force moves east from Gabr Saleh, crosses into Egypt below Sidi Omar; attacked by Brit; Brit capture Gialo Oasis; rept air successes at various points; map
